The Chinese mainland recorded 59 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Saturday, with 42 linked to local transmissions and 17 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Sunday. A total of 21 new asymptomatic cases were also recorded, and 459 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. Confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland now total 99,142, with the death toll unchanged since January at 4,636. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 12,452 (12,148 recoveries, 213 deaths) Macao: 77 (77 recoveries) Taiwan: 16,648 (13,742 recoveries, 848 deaths)